parameters.name: AppIds
parameters.description: The IDs of jobs that are submitted to YARN.

parameters.name: DateTime
parameters.description: Specify the date in the ISO 8601 standard. For example, 2023-01-01 represents January 1, 2023.

parameters.name: MaxResults
parameters.description: The maximum number of entries to return on each page.

parameters.name: NextToken
parameters.description: The pagination token that is used in the request to retrieve a new page of results.

parameters.name: OrderBy
parameters.description:
The field that you use to sort the query results. Valid values:

1.  startTime: the time when the job starts
2.  endTime: the time when the job ends
3.  vcoreUtilization: the vCPU utilization of the job
4.  memUtilization: the memory usage of the job
5.  vcoreSeconds: the aggregated number of vCPUs that are allocated to the job multiplied by the number of seconds the job has been running
6.  memSeconds: the aggregated amount of memory that is allocated to the job multiplied by the number of seconds the job has been running
7.  score: the score of the job

parameters.name: OrderType
parameters.description:
The order in which you want to sort the query results. Valid values:

*   ASC: the ascending order
*   DESC: the descending order

parameters.name: Queues
parameters.description: The YARN queues to which the jobs are submitted.

parameters.name: Types
parameters.description: The YARN engines to which the jobs are submitted.

parameters.name: Users
parameters.description: The users who submit the jobs.
